<p>I'm developing ASP.NET MVC 5 application that uses <a href="http://imageprocessor.org/" rel="nofollow">ImageProcessor</a> http module to serve responsive images:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;img src="@Url.MyExtMethodToAddParamsForImageProcessor(Model.Thumbnail)" alt="" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want my image urls to look cleaner so instead of</p>  <pre><code>image01.jpg?width=900&amp;quality=85&amp;watermark=bla-bla </code></pre>  <p>I'd like to have just</p>  <pre><code>image01.jpg?size=LA </code></pre>  <p>and then convert it at the server. According to <a href="http://www.iis.net/learn/extensions/url-rewrite-module/iis-url-rewriting-and-aspnet-routing" rel="nofollow">this article</a> url routing is the preferred method for new applications but I'm not sure how to configure it so that ImageProcessor is happy.</p>  <p>In other words, if I have an external ASP.NET http module added to <code>&lt;system.web&gt;</code> section how do I reroute a url to that module? I need somehow convert <code>\.jpg?size=(SM|ME|LA)</code> urls to urls the module expects.</p>